---
import Container from "@components/Container.astro";
import Footer from "@components/Footer.astro";
import GetAppButton from "@components/GetAppButton.astro";
import Page from "@layouts/Page.astro";
---

<Page
  title="Box Timer – Free EMOM Timer App for iPhone"
  description="Free EMOM timer app for iPhone and iPad. Set rounds and minute intervals with audio cues at every transition. Perfect for CrossFit. No ads, no subscriptions."
  url="https://boxtimer.app/emom-timer/"
  canonical="https://boxtimer.app/emom-timer/"
>
  <Container innerClass={"flex-col items-center"}>
    <div class="w-full sm:w-9/12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-sans font-bold">
        Free EMOM Timer for iPhone
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl font-light text-zinc-500 mt-4">
        The simple, ad-free timer for Every Minute On the Minute workouts
      </p>

      <div class="flex justify-center mt-12 mb-16">
        <GetAppButton id="get-app-button-emom-top" />
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-sans font-bold mt-16 mb-4">What is EMOM?</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">
        EMOM stands for <strong>Every Minute On the Minute</strong>. You
        perform a set number of reps at the start of each minute, then rest for
        whatever time remains before the next minute begins. The faster you
        finish your reps, the more rest you get — which makes pacing a built-in
        part of the workout.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-4">
        EMOM workouts are a staple of CrossFit programming and are popular for
        strength work, skill practice, and conditioning. They typically last
        <strong>10 to 20 minutes</strong> and can be done with barbells,
        dumbbells, kettlebells, or bodyweight movements.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-sans font-bold mt-16 mb-4">
        Why Box Timer for EMOM?
      </h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-outside ml-6 space-y-3">
        <li>
          <strong>Work-only intervals</strong> — Set round length with no
          separate rest period. The timer beeps every minute (or at your chosen
          interval) so you know when to start the next set.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Clear round counter</strong> — The display shows the current
          round number so you always know where you are in the workout.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Loud audio cues</strong> — Beeps signal each new minute even
          if you are not looking at the screen. Last 3 seconds of each round
          get warning beeps.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Large display</strong> — Read the timer from across the gym.
          Rotate to landscape for a full-screen view you can prop up next to
          your barbell.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Workout history</strong> — Save and pin your favorite EMOM
          setups. Reload a 10-minute EMOM or a 20-minute EMOM with one tap.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Free with no ads</strong> — No interruptions, no
          subscriptions, no paywalls.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-sans font-bold mt-16 mb-4">
        How to set up an EMOM timer
      </h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-outside ml-6 space-y-2">
        <li>Open Box Timer and tap <strong>Edit Timer</strong></li>
        <li>Select <strong>Interval</strong> as the timer type</li>
        <li>Set <strong>Rounds</strong> to your desired number (e.g. 10 for a 10-minute EMOM)</li>
        <li>Set <strong>Work</strong> to 1 minute and 0 seconds</li>
        <li>Set <strong>Rest</strong> to 0 minutes and 0 seconds</li>
        <li>Turn on <strong>Countdown</strong> if you want a 10-second lead-in</li>
        <li>Tap <strong>Save</strong>, then <strong>Start</strong></li>
      </ol>
      <p class="mt-4">
        See the full guide:
        <a
          class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800"
          href="/support/how-to-set-a-interval-timer-with-work-time-only/"
          >How to set an interval timer with work time only</a
        >
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-sans font-bold mt-16 mb-4">
        Popular EMOM formats
      </h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full mt-4">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th class="text-left pb-4 pr-4 font-bold">Format</th>
              <th class="text-left pb-4 pr-4 font-bold">Interval</th>
              <th class="text-left pb-4 font-bold">Rounds</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">10-minute EMOM</td>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">1 min</td>
              <td class="py-2">10</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">15-minute EMOM</td>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">1 min</td>
              <td class="py-2">15</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">20-minute EMOM</td>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">1 min</td>
              <td class="py-2">20</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">E2MOM (every 2 minutes)</td>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">2 min</td>
              <td class="py-2">10</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">E90S (every 90 seconds)</td>
              <td class="py-2 pr-4">1 min 30s</td>
              <td class="py-2">10</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="mt-4 text-zinc-500">
        All of these can be set up in Box Timer using the interval timer with
        rest set to zero.
      </p>

      <div class="flex justify-center mt-16 mb-8">
        <GetAppButton id="get-app-button-emom-bottom" />
      </div>

      <p class="mt-16">
        <strong>Related:</strong>
        <a
          class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800"
          href="/crossfit-timer/"
          >Free CrossFit Timer for iPhone</a
        >
        &nbsp;·&nbsp;
        <a
          class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800"
          href="/2026-best-workout-timers-iphone/"
          >Best Workout Timer Apps for iPhone in 2026</a
        >
      </p>
    </div>
  </Container>
  <Footer />
  <script type="application/ld+json">
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "HowTo",
      "name": "How to set up an EMOM timer on iPhone",
      "step": [
        { "@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Open Box Timer and tap Edit Timer" },
        { "@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Select Interval as the timer type" },
        { "@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Set Rounds to your desired number" },
        { "@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Set Work to 1 minute and 0 seconds" },
        { "@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Set Rest to 0 minutes and 0 seconds" },
        { "@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Turn on Countdown if you want a 10-second lead-in" },
        { "@type": "HowToStep", "name": "Tap Save, then Start" }
      ]
    }
  </script>
</Page>
